INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('3573', '8', 'Snow Pea, Scallion and Radish Saladon the side.Finish the meal with sweet-tart'),
('3573', '9', 'Avocado Frozen Yogurt.'),
('3575', '1', 'Put the cilantro, lime juice,  cup olive oil, onion, garlic, jalapeno, garlic powder, paprika, cumin, and salt and pepper in the bowl of a food processor.Blend until smooth.'),
('3575', '2', 'Put the puree in a bowl and set aside.Chop the halibut into small pieces.  Dry well with a paper towel.  Season with salt and pepper.Preheat a saute pan with 2 Tablespoons of olive oil.'),
('3575', '3', 'Add the halibut.  Cook until golden brown, about 8 minutes.'),
('3575', '4', 'Add the wine and cook until the wine evaporates, about 2 minutes.'),
('3575', '5', 'Add the cilantro mixture and cook for another minute to heat through.'),
('3575', '6', 'Heat the corn tortillas in a hot dry pan.'),
('3575', '7', 'Add the fish mixture to the tortilla.'),
('3575', '8', 'Garnish with cilantro, salsa, sour cream, cheese, and avocado.'),
('3577', '1', 'Rinse fish and pat dry; set aside. In a shallow dish, stir together the flour, salt, and pepper to taste. Dip each fillet in the flour mixture to coat.'),
('3577', '2', 'In a skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Cook the fish in the hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes per side or until golden.'),
('3577', '3', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, mustard, and dill. Set aside.'),
('3577', '4', 'Spread the dill mayonnaise evenly on the rolls.'),
('3577', '5', 'Place a fish fillet on each roll and top with tomato and onion slices'),
('3578', '1', 'Combine black pepper, red pepper flakes, cumin. Rub halibut with mixture; saut in olive oil until browned, about 3 minutes each side. Divide fish between tortillas; top each with half the lettuce, cheese, salsa, yogurt.'),
('3578', '2', 'Mix brown rice with tomatoes, jalapeo; serve with tacos.'),
('3578', '3', 'Combine black pepper, red pepper flakes, cumin. Rub halibut with mixture; saut in olive oil until browned, about 3 minutes each side. Divide fish between tortillas; top each with half the lettuce, cheese, salsa, yogurt.'),
('3578', '4', 'Mix brown rice with tomatoes, jalapeo; serve with tacos.'),
('3579', '1', 'Heat oven to 350F.'),
('3579', '2', 'Place fish in single layer in shallow baking dish.'),
('3579', '3', 'Bake 25 min. or until fish flakes easily with fork.  Flake fish; place in medium bowl.  Stir in 1 cup cheese, sour cream, dressing, onions, 1/4 cup olives, chilies and seasoning mix. Spoon down centers of tortillas; roll up.'),
('3579', '4', 'Pour half the enchilada sauce onto bottom of 13x9-inch pan.  Top with enchiladas, seam-sides down. Cover with remaining sauce and cheese.'),
('3579', '5', 'Bake 25 to 35 min. or until heated through.  Top with lettuce, tomatoes and remaining olives.'),
('3581', '1', 'Saute celery, carrots, and garlic in 3 tablespoons olive oil for 5 minutes.'),
('3581', '2', 'Remove from heat. Stir in milk, spinach, peas, Parmesan, eggs, parsley, Dijon mustard, salt, and flaked halibut.'),
('3581', '3', 'Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.'),
('3581', '4', 'Mix mashed potatoes with'),
('3581', '5', 'scallions and spread on top of the pie.'),
('3581', '6', 'Bake 40 minutes at 400 F.'),
('3582', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('3583', '1', 'Heat oven to 425F.'),
('3583', '2', 'Place fish on rimmed baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.'),
('3583', '3', 'Mix all remaining ingredients except bread crumbs; spoon over fish.  Top with crumbs.'),
('3583', '4', 'Bake 20 to 25 min. or until fish flakes easily with fork.'),
('3584', '1', 'There''s a lot of reasons, really. The whole eat local thing, of course. Giving the farmers all of my food dollar instead of processors and retailers, better food ...But also, food I have never seen before. New things. Every week. Like these, garlic scapes, at left. Softer, greener, garlicky flavor. Nice.And the greens. I got these from the Thai family that sells at the market. I have no idea what they are. The only explanation I got was, "We cook it with fish. There is no English word for them." Sold. Oh, they were good with fish, too. You can substitute baby bok choy or spinach. If I knew what the greens were, I''d be planting some!Asian-style Fish with Greens1 lb. halibut (or other sustainable white fish)Salt and pepper to taste1 tbs. canola oil, divided3 garlic scapes, or 2 cloves garlic, chopped1 bunch greens, or bok choyfor the sauce:1 cup miso soup1/2 cup honey1/4 cup soy sauce2 tsp. chopped ginger'),
('3584', '2', 'Place the sauce ingredients in a small sauce pan and heat to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer until sauce is reduced and thickened, about 15 minutes.'),
('3584', '3', 'Heat oven or grill. For oven, 350 degrees. Lightly oil the fish and salt and pepper.'),
('3584', '4', 'Bake for about 20 minutes or until fish is firm, opaque and flakes easily.'),
('3584', '5', 'Heat the rest of the canola oil in a skillet, medium high.'),
('3584', '6', 'Add the garlic and saute for two minutes.'),
('3584', '7', 'Add the greens and saute just until wilted.'),
('3584', '8', 'Serve the greens on bottom, fish on top of greens and drizzle on sauce. The sauce is also excellent for stir fry, such as asparagus.If anyone knows the name of these greens, please tell me!But Do Kids Eat This?I''ve ranted about the idea of "kid''s menus" and "kid food" limited to chicken fingers and mac and cheese are a myth before, so no need to go into that here. Did mine eat this? Definitely, and once her serving was finished, she ate most of mine for seconds. You just never know if you don''t try.Even if sometimes you don''t want to. Like the evening my spouse and I treated ourselves to a pound of wild caught salmon he smoked on the grill. The kiddo eyed her pork and noodles, pushed it away, and said, "I want THAT!" pointing at our $30-a-pound-once-a-year luxury.We looked at each other. Should we? I forked over a couple bites."I like it!" Kiddo exclaims. Of course she does. Good food really doesn''t have an age limit any more than someone telling me I''m too old for an ice cream cone.A couple tips on giving fish to your child, however, make sure it is one of the more sustainable choices for the environment, and for things like mercury contamination level. You can get a lot of information on this from Monterey Bay Aquarium''s Seafood Watch.'),
('3585', '1', 'Halve zucchini lengthwise and then cut into 1/2-inch slices.'),
('3585', '2', 'Pour about 3 to 4 tablespoons of olive oil into a large skillet and heat over medium-high heat.'),
('3585', '3', 'Add the zucchini and season generously with salt.'),
('3585', '4', 'Saute until zucchini starts to soften, but is not fully cooked, about 5 minutes.'),
('3585', '5', 'Remove from heat.'),
('3585', '6', 'Meanwhile, cut the fish into 1-inch cubes for the kabobs and place in a large mixing bowl.'),
('3585', '7', 'Add the tomatoes and remaining olive oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, salt, pepper, and oregano. Toss until fish and tomatoes are well coated.'),
('3585', '8', 'Add zucchini once cooled.'),
('3585', '9', 'Assemble skewers and pour the remaining marinade over them. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to grill. Skewers can be left to marinate for 30 minutes but no longer than 1 1/2 hours since the lemon juice will start to "cook" the fish.'),
('3585', '10', 'Heat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat.'),
('3585', '11', 'Grill skewers and baste with remaining marinade, turning once after several minutes on the first side, until fish is just cooked through but not flaking apart, about 7 to 9 minutes total.'),
('3585', '12', 'Serve immediately.'),
('3588', '1', 'In a large bowl, combine halibut, mayonnaise, tarragon, and Dijon. Toss to coat fish. Fold in celery, scallions, pimento, and hot sauce. Season, to taste, with salt and black pepper.'),
('3588', '2', 'Serve on buns with lettuce.'),
('3590', '1', 'Whisk together ingredients for white sauce and refrigerate until ready to use.'),
('3590', '2', 'Combine lime juice, oil and cumin in a shallow nonreactive dish small enough to just hold the fish.'),
('3590', '3', 'Add fish and turn to coat in the marinade. Season with salt and pepper and marinate fish at room temperature for 30 minutes. OR mix dry rub spices together and sprinkle on both sides of fish.Preheat grill to medium-hot.'),
('3590', '4', 'Brush grill grate with oil. Grill fish until just cooked through, about 3-5 minutes per side. Break fish into large pieces.Fill tortilla with fish and desired accompaniments.'),
('3590', '5', 'Drizzle with white sauce and squeeze fresh lime wedges over tacos.'),
('3591', '1', 'Mix first 7 ingredients in small bowl.'),
('3591', '2', 'Place zucchini, eggplant, tomatoes, peppers, and onion in large bowl.'),
('3591', '3', 'Add 1 tablespoon herb mixture and 1 tablespoon oil to vegetables. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Thread 1 mini pepper, 1 zucchini round, 1 eggplant piece, 1 tomato, 1 onion piece, and 1 more mini pepper onto each of 8 skewers. DO AHEAD Herb mixture and vegetables can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover separately and refrigerate.'),
('3591', '4', 'Place fish in medium bowl; sprinkle 2 tablespoons herb mixture over.'),
('3591', '5', 'Add 3 tablespoons oil, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, and garlic; sprinkle with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Cover and chill at least 1 hour and up to 2 hours, tossing occasionally.Simmer wine, remaining 1 tablespoon oil, and remaining 2 tablespoons lemon juice in small saucepan until reduced to 1/3 cup, about 3 minutes. Stir in remaining herb mixture. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside.Spray grill rack with nonstick spray; prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Divide fish cubes among remaining 4 skewers. Grill vegetable skewers until vegetables are slightly charred and tender, turning occasionally, 10 to 12 minutes. Grill fish skewers until fish is cooked through, turning occasionally, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('3591', '6', 'Place 1 fish skewer and 2 vegetable skewers on each plate.'),
('3591', '7', 'Drizzle sauce over.'),
('3592', '1', 'To make the marinade, combine all ingredients except fish in a small bowl.Arrange the fish in a glass or non-reactive dish just large enough to hold the fish and the marinade.'),
('3592', '2', 'Pour HALF the marinade over the fish and allow to sit at room temperature for 10-45 minutes (depending on how much time you have.)Preheat the grill or broiler until hot. If using the grill, place some oil in a small bowl and use it to grease the grill.'),
('3592', '3', 'Place fish skin-side down and grill about 3-5 minutes on each side, depending on thickness. Discard marinade that the fish was sitting in. Cook fish until it starts to flake, but is still rare inside.'),
('3592', '4', 'Transfer to a serving platter and pour the reserved marinade over each piece of fish and cover with a piece of foil for 5 minutes.'),
('3593', '1', 'Mix all ingredients in bowl; season with salt and pepper.'),
('3595', '1', 'Pour olive oil into an 11- to 12-inch frying pan over medium-high heat. Break pasta into 3- to 4-inch lengths and drop into oil; stir often until golden, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('3595', '2', 'Add onion, garlic, and turmeric; stir until onion is limp, 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('3595', '3', 'Stir in broth and tomatoes, including juice; cover and bring to a boil over high heat.'),
('3595', '4', 'Spread mixture level. Evenly distribute artichoke hearts and clams, if using, over pasta. Cover, reduce heat to medium, and cook for 5 minutes. Evenly distribute shrimp, fish, and peas over pasta. Cover and cook until clams have opened and fish is barely opaque in center of thickest part (cut to test), 5 to 8 minutes longer.'),
('3595', '5', 'Uncover and cook until pasta has absorbed most of the liquid and is beginning to brown on the bottom, 2 to 4 minutes.'),
('3595', '6', 'Add salt to taste.'),
('3595', '7', 'Garnish with lemon wedges to squeeze over seafood.'),
('3595', '8', 'Serve from pan.'),
('3596', '1', 'To make the fish, in a small bowl, whisk together the oil, lime juice, salt, and pepper.'),
('3596', '2', 'Pour over the fish and let marinate at room temperature for 20 minutes. Preheat a grill or grill pan over medium-high heat.In another small bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, and chipotle. Set aside.'),
('3596', '3', 'Remove fish from marinade and grill until cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.To prepare tacos, heat the tortillas on the grill or grill pan for 30 seconds on each side.Flake fish with a fork.'),
('3596', '4', 'Spread each tortilla with 1 tablespoons chipotle cream. Top with the fish, lettuce, corn, and cilantro and serve with lime wedges.'),
('3597', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine the first eight ingredients; let stand for 30 minutes. If grilling the fish, coat grill rack with nonstick cooking spray before starting the grill.'),
('3597', '2', 'Spread 1 tablespoon herbed butter over each halibut steak.'),
('3597', '3', 'Grill fish, butter side down, covered, over medium heat or broil, buttered side up, 4 in. from the heat for 5-1/2 minutes.'),
('3597', '4', 'Spread 1 tablespoon herbed butter over each halibut steak; turn and spread with remaining butter. Grill or broil 5-6 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3598', '1', 'In a small skillet, toast the cumin seeds over moderate heat until fragrant, about 2 minutes.'),
('3598', '2', 'Transfer to a spice grinder to cool, then grind.'),
('3598', '3', 'In a food processor or using a large mortar and pestle, finely chop the garlic.'),
('3598', '4', 'Add the cilantro and parsley and finely chop.'),
('3598', '5', 'Add the ground cumin, paprika, cayenne, salt and olive oil and mix just until combined.'),
('3598', '6', 'Pour 6 tablespoons of the charmoula into a large bowl for the halibut marinade; transfer the remaining charmoula to a medium bowl and stir in the lemon juice and vinegar.'),
('3598', '7', 'Light a grill or preheat the broiler.'),
('3598', '8', 'Add the halibut to the charmoula in the large bowl and toss.'),
('3598', '9', 'Cut the lemon slices in half. Thread the halibut, bay leaves and lemon pieces onto 10 long bamboo skewers, alternating the ingredients and beginning and ending with fish.'),
('3598', '10', 'Brush the grate with oil. Season the skewers with salt. Grill over a medium-hot fire or broil, turning occasionally, until the fish is just cooked through, 8 to 11 minutes.'),
('3598', '11', 'Transfer the skewers to a platter and serve right away, with the extra charmoula, the California Harissa and the Mint Yogurt Sauce.'),
('3599', '1', 'Bring 4 cups water, the ginger, and kombu to a boil in a large, wide pot. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 4 minutes. Turn off heat, sprinkle in bonito flakes, and let sit 3 minutes (flakes will sink). Strain broth through a cheesecloth-lined fine-mesh strainer into a bowl.'),
('3599', '2', 'Rinse pot, then pour in broth.'),
('3599', '3', 'Add leek and carrots. Bring to a simmer and cook 2 minutes.'),
('3599', '4', 'Add black cod and scallops; simmer 1 minute.'),
('3599', '5', 'Add shrimp and cook 2 minutes more.'),
('3599', '6', 'Whisk miso with lager in a small bowl.'),
('3599', '7', 'Remove stew from heat and carefully stir in miso mixture.'),
('3599', '8', 'Serve with lemon zest and shiso for topping if you like.'),
('3599', '9', '*Find kombu, a large seaweed sold dried, and bonito flakes with the Asian ingredients at well-stocked supermarkets and at natural-foods or Japanese markets. Find shiso, an aromatic herb, at Japanese markets and some farmers'' markets.'),
('3602', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).'),
('3602', '2', 'Place an oven rack about 5 inches from the heat source. Prepare a baking sheet with cooking spray.'),
('3602', '3', 'Arrange halibut on prepared baking sheet and bake until lightly browned, 4 to 6 minutes. Flip fillets, season with salt and black pepper, and continue cooking until flesh is opaque, 1 to 2 minutes more.'),
('3602', '4', 'Top each fillet with a mozzarella cheese slice, a basil leaf, and a tomato slice, respectively; repeat layers.'),
('3602', '5', 'Return halibut to oven and bake until cheese begins to melt, about 2 minutes.'),
('3602', '6', 'Whisk balsamic vinegar and olive oil together in a bowl; soon over halibut portions.'),
('3602', '7', 'Garnish with chopped basil to serve.'),
('3603', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375  degrees F (190 degrees C).'),
('3603', '2', 'Season the halibut with garlic powder, salt, and pepper; cook in microwave until slightly cooked, about 2 minutes.'),
('3603', '3', 'Mix together the green onion, bell pepper, cilantro, sour cream, mayonnaise and 1 cup Cheddar cheese in a bowl. Gently fold the halibut into the mixture.'),
('3603', '4', 'Prepare a 9x13 baking dish with cooking spray.'),
('3603', '5', 'Pour 1/2 of a can of enchilada sauce into the bottom of the baking dish.'),
('3603', '6', 'Pour 1 can of enchilada sauce into a bowl. Dip the tortillas, one at a time, into the sauce to lightly coat. Spoon the halibut in equal portions into the center of each tortilla. Make the enchiladas by tightly rolling the tortillas and place seam-side down in the baking dish.'),
('3603', '7', 'Pour the remaining enchilada sauce over top of the enchiladas. Sprinkle with 1 cup Cheddar cheese. Cover the dish with aluminum foil'),
('3603', '8', 'Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes. Top with avocado slices to serve.'),
('3604', '1', 'Combine cubed halibut, lime juice, lemon juice, tequila, minced jalapeno peppers, and 1 diced mango in a non-metallic bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 1 1/2 hours.'),
('3604', '2', 'After the ceviche has sat for 1 1/2 hours, add the green pepper, sweet onion, and red onion.'),
('3604', '3', 'Mix well, then recover and refrigerate another 30 minutes.'),
('3604', '4', 'Fold in the remaining diced mango, cilantro, and parsley; season to taste with salt before serving.'),
('3605', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees.'),
('3605', '2', 'Place the garlic, herbs, salt and pepper in the bowl of a mini-food processor and process until the herbs are finely chopped.'),
('3605', '3', 'Add the olive oil and process until well combined.'),
('3605', '4', 'Add lemon zest and pulse once or twice.'),
('3605', '5', 'Place each piece of fish in the center of a sheet of parchment.'),
('3605', '6', 'Spread a heaping spoonful of the herb mixture on top of each piece of fish.Bring 2 opposite sides of the parchment together and fold. Continue to fold all the way down until you reach the fish. Twist both ends of the parchment so that it looks like a hard candy wrapper.'),
('3605', '7', 'Place each packet on a baking sheet and bake for 12-15 minutes based on the thickness of the fish.'),
('3605', '8', 'Transfer each packet to a plate and use caution when opening  the steam will be very hot!'),
('3606', '1', 'For the Veracruz sauce, fry the onions and garlic in a couple tablespoons of olive oil until soft and translucent.'),
('3606', '2', 'Add the tomatoes, chili, olives, capers, oregano, marjoram and bay leaf. Cook over medium high heat for about 20 minutes to reduce the amount of liquid and concentrate the flavours. Taste it and add salt as needed (about 1/2 tsp of kosher salt should do it).To get the fish crisp and brown on the outside, you need to get the surface very dry, use paper towels and try to get as much moisture off the surface as possible. Start heating a cast iron pan over medium high heat.When the pan is very hot, lightly salt and pepper both sides of the fish.'),
('3606', '3', 'Add a splash of oil to the pan and swirl to coat.'),
('3606', '4', 'Put the fish into the pan and do not touch until it starts turning brown around the edges and no longer sticks to the pan. Gently flip and brown the other side. If you''re cooking thicker cuts of fish, the center should read 125 degrees F on an instant read thermometer.When it''s cooked, plate the fish. Stir the minced cilantro into the sauce. Cover the the fish with the Veracruz sauce and garnish with some spare cilantro leaves and a wedge of lime.'),
('3607', '1', 'Combine salsa ingredients.'),
('3607', '2', 'Heat grill.'),
('3607', '3', 'Cut fish into 4 pieces.'),
('3607', '4', 'Whisk together oil, lime juice, chili powder.'),
('3607', '5', 'Brush mixture onto both sides of each fillet; season with salt and pepper. Grill 3 to 4 minutes on each side until cooked through. Fill each tortilla with 1 fillet, flaked into pieces, and 1/4 cup each cabbage and salsa; top with 2 tbsp sour cream.'),
('3607', '6', 'Serve with 1/2 cup beans.'),
('3607', '7', 'Combine salsa ingredients.'),
('3607', '8', 'Heat grill.'),
('3607', '9', 'Cut fish into 4 pieces.'),
('3607', '10', 'Whisk together oil, lime juice, chili powder.'),
('3607', '11', 'Brush mixture onto both sides of each fillet; season with salt and pepper. Grill 3 to 4 minutes on each side until cooked through. Fill each tortilla with 1 fillet, flaked into pieces, and 1/4 cup each cabbage and salsa; top with 2 tbsp sour cream.'),
('3607', '12', 'Serve with 1/2 cup beans.'),
('3608', '1', 'Put the green mango, bel pepper, onion, cilantro, salt, lime juice, chili and hot sauce in a bowl and toss to combine.Use a paper towel to dry the surface of the fish and salt and pepper. Grill over charcoal, broil or pan-fry.To serve, just top the cooked fillet with a dollop of green mango pico de gallo.'),
('3610', '1', 'Bring a pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('3610', '2', 'Cut the zucchini lengthwise down the 4 sides, taking off all of the green and about 1/2 inch of the white in each of the 4 pieces. Discard the white, inner section.'),
('3610', '3', 'Cut the rest into -inch dice. Blanch until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('3610', '4', 'Drain, plunge into ice water, and drain again. Set aside.'),
('3610', '5', 'Take off the outer 2 layers of fennel and save the rest for another use. Trim away any thin, flexible sections near the edge of the fennel.'),
('3610', '6', 'Cut the firm, thick part into -inch dice. Blanch as with the zucchini.'),
('3610', '7', 'Scrape all pulp and pith from the preserved lemon and cut the yellow rind into fine julienne. Blanch for 1 minute, refresh in ice water, drain again, and set aside. (The recipe can be made to this point up to several hours ahead.)'),
('3610', '8', 'Put 2 cups of nage and the mussel stock in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.'),
('3610', '9', 'Add the saffron and boil for 2 to 3 minutes. Set aside.'),
('3610', '10', 'Bring 3 cups of nage to a boil in a 10-inch-wide pot. Season both sides of the halibut with salt and pepper.'),
('3610', '11', 'Add the halibut to the pot and adjust the heat so the liquid just simmers. Poach until a metal skewer inserted into the center of the halibut meets only a little resistance, 5 to 6 minutes, and the skewer, when left in the fish for 5 seconds, feels barely warm when touched to your lip. The halibut will be rare (thinner steaks will be ready sooner). Take the steaks out of the liquid as soon as they are done.'),
('3610', '12', 'Meanwhile, put the zucchini, fennel, preserved lemon, tomatoes, and shallot in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat.'),
('3610', '13', 'Add the capers and the olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Just warm the vegetables through, about 2 minutes; do not let them cook further.'),
('3610', '14', 'To serve, cut the 4 basil leaves across into thin strips. Stir the olives into the vegetables and squeeze the  lemon over them. Pull the skin off the halibut. Reheat the saffron broth, if necessary.'),
('3610', '15', 'Put the halibut in the center of the plates and arrange the vegetables over and around the steaks.'),
('3610', '16', 'Pour the saffron broth around the halibut. Scatter the basil over and around the fish and serve immediately.'),
('3610', '17', 'var article'),
('3610', '18', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('3610', '19', 'article'),
('3610', '20', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('3611', '1', 'Heat grill to medium-high heat.'),
('3611', '2', 'Spoon 1/2 cup rice onto center of each of 4 large sheets of heavy-duty foil with sides slightly rolled up.'),
('3611', '3', 'Pour 1/2 cup warm water over each mound of rice; top with 1 fish fillet.  Arrange spinach around fish; drizzle with dressing.'),
('3611', '4', 'Bring up foil sides. Double fold top and ends to seal each packet, leaving room for heat circulation inside.'),
('3611', '5', 'Grill 10 min. or until fish flakes easily with fork.'),
('3611', '6', 'Cut slits in foil to release steam before opening packets; top with cheese.'),
('3612', '1', 'Core the tomatoes, cut into pieces, and place in a blender. Blend until pureed. Strain through a sieve into a bowl. You should have about 1 cups pure.'),
('3612', '2', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil in a nonreactive medium saucepan until hot.'),
('3612', '3', 'Add the garlic and saut briefly until light brown.'),
('3612', '4', 'Add the tomato puree and bring to a boil. Simmer gently about 5 minutes. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl. Discard the solids.'),
('3612', '5', 'Rinse out the saucepan, return the tomato juice to the pan, and bring to a boil. Simmer and strain twice more until the tomato juice is as thick as heavy cream, about 15 minutes total cooking time. Be sure to lower the heat as the mixture thickens to prevent scorching. You should have about  cup of very smooth tomato juice.'),
('3612', '6', 'Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and taste for salt and pepper.'),
('3612', '7', 'Pour 1 tablespoon of the olive oil into a small, clean glass bottle with a stopper and swirl to coat the inside. Strain the tomato juice into the bottle.'),
('3612', '8', 'Let it cool to room temperature.'),
('3612', '9', 'Add 2 tablespoons of the olive oil. Do not shake or mix!'),
('3612', '10', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add salt.'),
('3612', '11', 'Add the corn and cook just until tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('3612', '12', 'Remove and set aside. Cook the beans in the same water just until tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('3612', '13', 'Drain. If using favas, peel them. When the corn is cool enough to handle, cut the kernels from the cobs. Toss together in a bowl.'),
('3612', '14', 'In a clean jar with a lid, shake together the vinegar, tarragon, 3 tablespoons of the prosciutto bits, and 6 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('3612', '15', 'Pour enough of the dressing onto the corn and beans to coat, toss well, and taste for seasoning. Adjust with salt, pepper, and more dressing as necessary. Set aside to marinate for about 15 minutes.'),
('3612', '16', 'Season the fish on both sides with salt and pepper.'),
('3612', '17', 'Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large saut pan over medium-high heat until hot.'),
('3612', '18', 'Add the fish and cook until brown on the first side, about 3 minutes. Turn and continue to cook until opaque throughout, about 3 minutes longer.'),
('3612', '19', 'Remove from the pan and keep warm.'),
('3612', '20', 'When ready to serve, pile the corn mixture on a platter or divide among 4 large plates. Arrange the fish on top of the salads. Shake the tomato vinaigrette bottle gently. You do not want the mixture to emulsify, but to have separate droplets suspended within the oil.'),
('3612', '21', 'Spoon or shake about 1 tablespoon of the broken tomato vinaigrette on each piece of halibut and then drizzle or shake more tomato vinaigrette around the edges of the platter or plates.'),
('3612', '22', 'Garnish with the remaining prosciutto bits.'),
('3612', '23', 'var article'),
('3612', '24', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('3612', '25', 'article'),
('3612', '26', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0;'),
('3615', '1', 'Place the olive oil, onion, and garlic in a heavy pot over low heat and cook, stirring, until the onions are very soft, 15 minutes.'),
('3615', '2', 'Add the cardamom, saffron, lemon juice, cinnamon stick, orange zest, broth, and salt and pepper. Raise the heat to medium-high and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer, partially covered, for 10 minutes. Then stir in the chickpeas, raisins, and tomatoes.'),
('3615', '3', 'Add the parsley and the  cup mint and simmer, partially covered, shaking the pan occasionally; for 15 minutes.'),
('3615', '4', 'Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 400F.'),
('3615', '5', 'Remove the cinnamon stick and the orange zest from the vegetable mixture.'),
('3615', '6', 'Place the cooked vegetables in a 13  9-inch baking dish and arrange the halibut steaks on top. Spoon some of the vegetable liquid over the fish.'),
('3615', '7', 'Bake until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily when tested with a fork, 15 minutes.'),
('3615', '8', 'Serve the fish and vegetables over couscous and sprinkle with the remaining 2 tablespoons chopped mint.'),
('3615', '9', 'var article'),
('3615', '10', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
('3615', '11', 'article'),
