('3616', '1', 'Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.'),
('3616', '2', 'Add onion, carrot, celery, garlic, and jalapeo to pan; saut 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in broth, potato, wine, cilantro, and tomatoes; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 15 minutes or until potato is tender.'),
('3616', '3', 'Add fish and shrimp; cook an additional 5 minutes or until fish and shrimp are done. Ladle 2 1/2 cups stew into each of 4 bowls; serve with lime wedges.'),
('3616', '4', 'Garnish with cilantro sprigs, if desired.'),
('3617', '1', 'Core the tomatoes, cut into pieces, and place in a blender. Blend until pureed. Strain through a sieve into a bowl. You should have about 2 1/2 cups puree. If fresh tomatoes are not available use canned.'),
('3617', '2', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the olive oil in a non-reactive medium saucepan until hot.'),
('3617', '3', 'Add the garlic and saute briefly until light brown.'),
('3617', '4', 'Add the tomato puree and bring to a boil. Simmer gently about 5 minutes. Strain through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl. Discard the solids. Rinse out the saucepan, return the tomato juice to the pan, and bring to a boil. Simmer and strain twice more until the tomato juice is as thick as heavy cream, about 15 minutes total cooking time. Be sure to lower the heat as the mixture thickens to prevent scorching. You should have about 1/4 cup of very smooth tomato juice.'),
('3617', '5', 'Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice and taste for salt and pepper.'),
('3617', '6', 'Pour 1 tablespoon of the olive oil into a small, clean glass bottle with a stopper and swirl to coat the inside. Coat the glass bottle with olive oil and the funnel before straining tomatoes so they don''t stick. Strain the tomato juice into the bottle.'),
('3617', '7', 'Let it cool to room temperature.'),
('3617', '8', 'Add olive oil - mixture should be half olive oil and half tomato. Do not shake or mix!'),
('3617', '9', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add salt. Blanche the corn and cook just until tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('3617', '10', 'Remove and set aside. Cook the beans in the same water just until tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('3617', '11', 'Drain. If using favas, peel them. When the corn is cool enough to handle, cut the kernels from the cobs. Toss together in a bowl.;'),
('3617', '12', 'In a clean jar with a lid, shake together minced tarragon, 2 tablespoons of the bacon, and 25 percent of Champagne vinegar and 75 percent olive oil.'),
('3617', '13', 'Pour enough of the dressing onto the corn and beans to coat, toss well, and taste for seasoning. Adjust with salt, pepper, and more dressing as necessary. Set aside to marinate for about 15 minutes.;'),
('3617', '14', 'Season the fish on both sides with salt and pepper.'),
('3617', '15', 'Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large saute pan over medium-high heat until hot. Put presentation side of the fish (non-skin side) in pan first as it gets the best caramelization. Cook until brown on the first side, about 3 minutes. When you see it getting opague around the edges, give it another minute and flip sides. Cook another minute on other side.'),
('3617', '16', 'Remove from pan and place on cookie sheet for a bit while you enjoy your appetizer with company. Just before you''re ready to serve it, put it in a preheated 450 degree F oven for about 30 seconds.;'),
('3619', '1', 'Heat oil in a deep skillet or Dutch oven over medium high heat.'),
('3619', '2', 'Add onions, bay leaf, oregano, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper and cook until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes.'),
('3619', '3', 'Add garlic, green pepper and tomato paste and stir together for 2 minutes.'),
('3619', '4', 'Add red and white wine and simmer until reduced by half.'),
('3619', '5', 'Add chicken stock and clam juice, along with crushed tomatoes. Bring to a boil and reduce to simmer. Cover and cook for 30-60 minutes. Stir in basil and parsley and add seafood. Increase heat to bring to a simmer and cook until seafood is cooked through and mussels have opened, about 5-10 minutes.Facebook'),
('3619', '6', 'Twitter'),
('3619', '7', 'Google'),
('3619', '8', 'Pinterest'),
('3619', '9', 'Pocket'),
('3619', '10', 'Email9 Comments  Comments Feed'),
('3619', '11', 'Name (required)Mail (will not be published) (required)Website Previous'),
('3619', '12', 'Next'),
('3620', '1', 'In a 3- to 4-quart pan over high heat, bring about 1 quart water to a boil.'),
('3620', '2', 'Add potatoes. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender when pierced, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('3620', '3', 'Drain; keep warm.'),
('3620', '4', 'Meanwhile, rinse fish, scallops, and shrimp; pat dry.'),
('3620', '5', 'Cut fish into 1/4-inch-thick slices about 2 inches long.'),
('3620', '6', 'Cut scallops crosswise into 1/4-inch-thick slices.'),
('3620', '7', 'Cut shrimp in half lengthwise. Arrange fish, scallops, and shrimp on a flat dish.'),
('3620', '8', 'In a 3-quart metal chafing dish or pan over high heat, bring all the broth to a boil. If using a 2-quart fondue pan, fill it halfway with boiling broth (keep remaining broth hot; cover and set over lowest heat on a range).'),
('3620', '9', 'Set container over an ignited alcohol or canned solid-fuel flame. Adjust for maximum heat.'),
('3620', '10', 'Place potatoes, seafood, rouille, and croutons alongside.'),
('3620', '11', 'Spear potatoes or seafood, 1 piece at a time, on fondue forks or thin skewers (metal or wood) and immerse in broth. Cook potatoes until warm or hot, and seafood until barely opaque in thickest part, 30 seconds to 1 minute. Dip hot foods into rouille to taste, or spread rouille onto croutons to eat. If broth stops simmering, return to high heat on a range burner until boiling. Return to fondue burner. As broth in 2-quart pan evaporates, add remaining broth.'),
('3620', '12', 'When potatoes and seafood are consumed, ladle cooking broth into bowls.'),
('3620', '13', 'Spread any remaining croutons with remaining rouille; eat while sipping broth.'),
('3621', '1', 'Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan.'),
('3621', '2', 'Add rice and salt. Cover and reduce heat to low. Cook 15 minutes, then turn off heat and let sit 5 minutes. Fluff with a fork and cover to keep warm until ready to serve.'),
('3621', '3', 'Meanwhile, bring 1 in. of water to a boil in a large saucepan. Peel sweet potato and cut into 1/2-in. cubes. Put in a steamer basket over boiling water. Cover and steam until tender, about 10 minutes. Set aside.'),
('3621', '4', 'While sweet potato is cooking, spoon about 1/4 cup from top of coconut milk in each can (the thick opaque layer) and put in a 4- to 5-qt. pot or deep saut pan.'),
('3621', '5', 'Add curry paste and whisk until smoothly blended. Stir mixture over medium heat until nearly dry, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('3621', '6', 'Reduce heat to medium-low and add remaining coconut milk, lime zest, fish sauce, and brown sugar. Simmer 5 minutes.'),
('3621', '7', 'Meanwhile, cut fish into 1 1/2-in. cubes. Increase heat to medium; add fish and spinach. Cover and cook until fish is no longer translucent, 5 to 7 minutes.'),
('3621', '8', 'Chop basil and mint and stir into stew along with sweet potato cubes.'),
('3621', '9', 'Serve with rice and lime wedges.'),
('3622', '1', 'Heat grill to high (450 to 550).'),
('3622', '2', 'Mix seasonings in a small bowl. Put halibut on a rimmed baking sheet; coat with oil. Sprinkle with seasonings. Thread fish on 6 to 8 slender metal skewers. Oil cooking grate, using tongs and a wad of oiled paper towels.'),
('3622', '3', 'Grill fish, covered, turning once, until just cooked through, 3 to 4 minutes total. Fill tortillas with lettuce, fish, and salad.'),
('3622', '4', 'Serve with yogurt sauce.'),
('3622', '5', '*If tortillas are very thin, buy double the amount and stack 2 per taco.'),
('3625', '1', 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).'),
('3625', '2', 'Lightly butter 1 sheet of phyllo dough. Lay another sheet directly on top of the first sheet, and lightly butter it. Repeat with remaining 2 sheets of phyllo.'),
('3625', '3', 'Cut sheets in half.'),
('3625', '4', 'Season halibut fillets with salt and pepper.'),
('3625', '5', 'Place a fillet near the bottom edge of one of the halved sheets of phyllo. Sprinkle with dill. Fold in the sides of the phyllo, then roll the fillet.'),
('3625', '6', 'Place on a baking sheet, and lightly brush with butter. Repeat with remaining fillet.'),
('3625', '7', 'Bake in a preheated oven until pastry is puffed and golden brown, about 12 to 15 minutes.'),
('3625', '8', 'Meanwhile, bring lemon juice to a boil in a small saucepan over high heat. Boil until almost evaporated. Reduce heat to medium, and stir in cream. Simmer until the cream thickens somewhat. Stir in green onions, and season with salt and pepper.'),
('3625', '9', 'Serve halibut on a pool of sauce.'),
('3626', '1', 'Rinse fish and pat dry; coat pieces with about 2 teaspoons olive oil. Sprinkle lightly all over with salt and pepper. Set a 10- to 12-inch nonstick frying pan with ovenproof handle over high heat; when hot, set fish in pan and cook until lightly browned on the bottom, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('3626', '2', 'Transfer pan with fish to a 350 regular or convection oven and bake until fish is barely opaque but still moist-looking in center of thickest part (cut to test), 7 to 9 minutes.'),
('3626', '3', 'Meanwhile, rinse and drain mushrooms; trim off and discard stems for shiitakes (tough stem ends only for portabellas).'),
('3626', '4', 'Cut mushrooms into 1/2-inch chunks.'),
('3626', '5', 'In an 8- to 10-inch nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat, stir mushrooms and garlic in 1 teaspoon oil until mushrooms are limp, about 5 minutes.'),
('3626', '6', 'Add broth, tomato sauce, and soybeans; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until soybeans are tender to bite, about 5 minutes. Stir in 1 tablespoon chives.'),
('3626', '7', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('3626', '8', 'Mound a fourth of the soybean mixture in the center of each of four dinner plates. Top each mound with a piece of fish, pan-browned side up, and spoon Kabocha coulis equally around soybean mixture. Gently shake each plate to level coulis.'),
('3626', '9', 'Garnish fish with remaining tablespoon chives and scatter chopped basil over coulis if desired.'),
('3626', '10', 'Add more salt and pepper to taste.'),
('3627', '1', 'In a small bowl, mix vinegar, olive oil, cilantro, garlic, cumin seed, 3/4 teaspoon salt, and chilies to taste.'),
('3627', '2', 'Rinse fish and pat dry. In a heavy zip-lock plastic bag (1-gal. size), combine fish and 1/3 cup of the vinegar mixture.'),
('3627', '3', 'Let stand, turning occasionally, for about 15 minutes.'),
('3627', '4', 'Meanwhile, rinse and drain cabbage.'),
('3627', '5', 'Cut through core into quarters; cut out and discard core sections. Slice each quarter lengthwise into thin shreds to make about 6 cups. In a large bowl, mix shredded cabbage, onion, and 1/2 cup of the vinegar mixture.'),
('3627', '6', 'Add salt to taste.'),
('3627', '7', 'Lift fish from marinade (discard marinade) and place on an oiled grill over a solid bed of hot coals or high heat on a gas grill (you can hold your hand at grill level only 2 to 3 seconds); close lid on gas grill. Cook fish, turning once, until barely opaque but still moist-looking in center of thickest part (cut to test), 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('3627', '8', 'Mound cilantro-chili slaw equally on four dinner plates. Top each mound with a piece of hot or warm grilled fish.'),
('3627', '9', 'Drizzle remaining dressing equally over fish.'),
('3627', '10', 'Add salt to taste.'),
('3629', '1', 'Finely chop basil and shallot in mini food processor.'),
('3629', '2', 'Add butter, 2 tablespoons at a time, and process until blended, stopping occasionally to scrape down sides.'),
('3629', '3', 'Transfer to small bowl; stir in lemon peel and season basil-shallot butter with salt.'),
('3629', '4', 'Prepare barbecue (medium heat). Rub fish fillets on both sides with olive oil. Grill until fillets are just opaque in center, about 4 minutes per side.'),
('3629', '5', 'Transfer fish to plates. Immediately spread some basil-shallot butter over fish.'),
('3629', '6', 'Serve, passing additional basilshallot butter alongside.'),
('3630', '1', 'In a large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons of the olive oil over moderately high heat. Season the shrimp and monkfish with salt and pepper and add to the skillet. Cook for 6 minutes, turning once, until barely opaque throughout.'),
('3630', '2', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('3630', '3', 'In the same skillet, heat the remaining 3 tablespoons of olive oil over moderate heat.'),
('3630', '4', 'Add the tomatoes and cook for 3 minutes. Stir in the garlic, 1 tablespoon of the parsley, the serrano chile and the paprika.'),
('3630', '5', 'Add the chicken stock, clam juice and saffron, season with salt and bring to a boil.'),
('3630', '6', 'Add the capellini and cook, stirring occasionally, until the pasta is al dente and has absorbed most of the sauce, about 5 minutes. Return the shrimp and monkfish to the skillet along with any accumulated juices and toss well.'),
('3630', '7', 'Transfer the pasta to bowls and garnish with the remaining 1 tablespoon of parsley.'),
('3630', '8', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('3631', '1', 'In a 10- to 12-inch nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat, stir onion in olive oil until limp, about 1 minute.'),
('3631', '2', 'Add fish and gently stir until opaque on outside, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('3631', '3', 'Add lemon juice and 2 tablespoons oregano (2 teaspoons if using dried) and cook, gently stirring occasionally, until most of the liquid has evaporated and fish is opaque but still moist-looking in center (cut to test), 1 to 2 minutes. Gently stir in tomatoes and add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('3631', '4', 'Lay 4 tortillas flat on a 14- by 17-inch nonstick baking sheet (if you don''t have a nonstick sheet, coat a regular one lightly with cooking oil spray). Divide half the fish mixture among tortillas and spread level to within 1/2 inch of edges. Sprinkle a third of the cheese evenly over fish. Lay another tortilla on each stack and top equally with remaining fish mixture and another third of the cheese. Cover with remaining tortillas and sprinkle remaining cheese over the top.'),
('3631', '5', 'Bake in a 400 regular or convection oven until cheese on top is beginning to brown, 10 to 12 minutes.'),
('3631', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a small bowl, mix crema with remaining tablespoon oregano (1 teaspoon if using dried). With a wide spatula, transfer fish stacks to plates. Top equally with avocado slices and crema mixture.'),
('3631', '7', 'Garnish with lemon wedges to squeeze over stacks to taste.'),
('3633', '1', 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Lightly grease a medium baking dish.'),
('3633', '2', 'In a bowl, mix the Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream, flour, lemon juice, onion, and cayenne pepper.'),
('3633', '3', 'Arrange the halibut steaks in the prepared baking dish, and cover with the Cheddar cheese mixture.'),
('3633', '4', 'Bake 10 minutes in the preheated oven. Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C), and continue baking 15 minutes, or until fish is easily flaked with a fork.'),
('3634', '1', 'In a shallow dish, mix the olive oil, butter, lemon juice, dry mustard, salt, and pepper.'),
('3634', '2', 'Place the cubed halibut in the dish, and allow to marinate for 45 minutes in the refrigerator.'),
('3634', '3', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),
('3634', '4', 'Transfer the halibut and marinade mixture to a casserole dish.'),
('3634', '5', 'Spread the sour cream over the halibut, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, and top with French fried onions.'),
('3634', '6', 'Bake 15 minutes in the preheated oven, or until fish is easily flaked with a fork and marinade mixture is bubbly.'),
('3635', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),
('3635', '2', 'In a saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir the Cheddar cheese, Parmesan cheese, and milk until melted and well blended.'),
('3635', '3', 'Mix in the flour and water, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.'),
('3635', '4', 'Layer the spinach in the bottom of a baking dish. Arrange the halibut steaks over the spinach, and season with salt and pepper.'),
('3635', '5', 'Pour the cheese sauce mixture over the halibut.'),
('3635', '6', 'Bake 45 minutes in the preheated oven, until the fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3636', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a large, deep pot over medium heat.'),
('3636', '2', 'Saute the garlic and onion until they become aromatic, but not browned.'),
('3636', '3', 'Add in the diced tomatoes, tomato paste, and chili flakes and continue to stir for about 1 minute.'),
('3636', '4', 'Pour in the white wine and water and simmer on low heat. Cover and cook for about 30 minutes.Turn the heat up to high and add in the all the ingredients in Seafood and the parsley leaves. As soon as the clams and mussels are open, the stew is ready.'),
('3636', '5', 'Add salt to taste and serve immediately.'),
('3637', '1', 'Preheat an oven to 375F. Lightly oil a baking dish just large enough to hold the fillets snugly in a single layer.'),
('3637', '2', 'Place the fillets in the prepared baking dish, season lightly with salt and pepper, and drizzle with the wine. Arrange the tomato slices on top of the fish, overlapping them slightly if necessary.In a small bowl, stir together 2 Tbs. of the olive oil, the garlic, tarragon, parsley and thyme. Spoon the herb mixture evenly over the tomatoes, season with salt and pepper, and sprinkle with the bread crumbs.'),
('3637', '3', 'Drizzle with the remaining 1 Tbs. olive oil.'),
('3637', '4', 'Bake until the bread crumbs are browned on top and the fish is opaque throughout, 25 to 30 minutes.'),
('3637', '5', 'Serve immediately, directly from the baking dish.'),
('3637', '6', 'Serves 4.Adapted from Williams-Sonoma Fish for Dinner (Weldon Owen, 2009).'),
('3639', '1', 'Pour olive oil into a 5- to 6-quart pan over medium-high heat; when hot, add onion and garlic and stir often until onion is limp, 3 to 5 minutes.'),
('3639', '2', 'Add wine, tomatoes (with their juice if canned), tomato paste, basil, and pepper; bring mixture to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat and simmer, stirring often, for 10 minutes.'),
('3639', '3', 'Add salt to taste.'),
('3639', '4', 'Meanwhile, rinse and drain fish, shrimp, scallops, and crab; cut fish into 1- to 2-inch pieces. Scrub clams. Gently stir fish, shrimp, scallops, and clams into tomato broth; cover and simmer just until fish, shrimp, and scallops are opaque but still moist-looking in center of thickest part (cut to test) and clams have popped open, 7 to 9 minutes. Discard any clams that don''t open.'),
('3639', '5', 'Add crab and press gently to immerse in broth; cover and cook just until hot, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('3639', '6', 'Ladle cioppino into wide bowls and sprinkle with parsley.'),
('3639', '7', 'Serve with bread and lemon wedges.'),
('3640', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).'),
('3640', '2', 'Place halibut in a baking dish. In a medium bowl, mix together mayonnaise, shredded Cheddar cheese, shredded Jack cheese, dill, and mustard.'),
('3640', '3', 'Spread cheese mixture over halibut. Sprinkle more dill on top if you like.'),
('3640', '4', 'Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until fish is done, and cheese is golden brown and bubbly.'),
('3643', '1', 'Crush cardamom pods; remove black seed.'),
('3643', '2', 'In a 1- to 1 1/2-quart pan, mix cardamom seed, carrot juice, 1 1/2 teaspoons vinegar, cornstarch, and sugar until well blended. Stir over high heat until mixture boils; reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, until reduced to 1/2 cup, 7 to 9 minutes. Cover pan and remove from heat; let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Taste, and add salt and more vinegar if desired.'),
('3643', '3', 'Pour sauce through a fine strainer into a bowl.'),
('3643', '4', 'Meanwhile, rinse fish, pat dry, and cut into 4 equal portions. Rub fish all over with olive oil and sprinkle lightly with salt. Set a 10- to 12-inch nonstick frying pan (with ovenproof handle) over high heat. When pan is hot, add fish and turn as needed to brown on both sides, 2 to 3 minutes total. Sprinkle pepper evenly over fish.'),
('3643', '5', 'Put pan with fish in a 400 oven; bake until fish is opaque but still moist-looking in center of thickest part (cut to test), 5 to 7 minutes.'),
('3643', '6', 'Transfer fish to rimmed plates. Spoon sauce evenly around fish and sprinkle with chives.'),
('3644', '1', 'Bring a small pot of salted water to a boil over high heat.'),
('3644', '2', 'Add the broccoli rabe and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('3644', '3', 'Transfer the cooked broccoli rabe to an ice bath and let cool, about 3 minutes. Shake off the excess water and transfer to a food processor.'),
('3644', '4', 'Add the garlic, walnuts, honey, salt, and pepper process until smooth. With the machine running gradually pour in the extra-virgin olive oil.'),
('3644', '5', 'Transfer the pesto to a small bowl and stir in the Parmesan. Cover and set aside.;'),
('3644', '6', 'In a medium, heavy skillet, heat the olive oil and vegetable oil over medium-low heat. Using a deep-fry thermometer, heat the oil to 200 degrees F. Reduce the heat to low to sustain the 200 degree F temperature. Season the fish with salt and pepper. Gently place the fish in the oil making sure it is submerged beneath the surface. Poach the fish until just cooked through, about 6 to 7 minutes.;'),
('3644', '7', 'Place about 1/2 cup of Broccoli Rabe Pesto on a serving plate and gently smooth out to make a bed for the fish. Using a slotted fish spatula gently transfer the cooked fish from the poaching oil to the serving plate, placing the fish on top of the bed of pesto.'),
('3644', '8', 'Serve immediately.;'),
('3645', '1', 'Preheat a grill pan or indoor grill to high heat or, prepare outdoor grill.'),
('3645', '2', 'Drizzle halibut with extra-virgin olive oil to keep fish from sticking to the grill pan or grill. Season fish with salt and pepper, to your taste.'),
('3645', '3', 'Roll lime on the counter top to get juices flowing. Also, any under ripe citrus may be placed in a microwave oven for 10 seconds at high setting to induce the juices to flow. Grill fish 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until opaque. Squeeze the juice of 1 lime down over the fish and remove from the grill pan or grill. Flake fish into large chunks with a fork.'),
('3645', '4', 'While fish is cooking, in a blender or food processor, combine avocado flesh, lemon juice, cayenne pepper, yogurt and salt. Process guacamole sauce until smooth.'),
('3645', '5', 'Remove guacamole sauce to a bowl and stir in diced tomatoes and chopped scallions. Shred lettuce and reserve.'),
('3645', '6', 'When fish comes off the grill pan or grill, blister and heat soft taco wraps. To assemble, break up fish and pile some of the meat into soft shells and slather with guacamole sauce. Top with shredded lettuce, fold tacos over and eat!'),
('3648', '1', 'Brush the inside of each pineapple shell with adobo sauce. Divide seafood mixture evenly between each pineapple shell; sprinkle with cilantro.'),
('3648', '2', 'Spread pineapple mixture over seafood, and pour over any remaining adobo sauce. Wrap crowns of pineapple with foil and transfer pineapples to prepared baking sheets.'),
('3648', '3', 'Bake for 20 minutes.'),
('3649', '1', 'Mix first 7 ingredients in small bowl.'),
('3649', '2', 'Place zucchini, eggplant, tomatoes, peppers, and onion in large bowl.'),
('3649', '3', 'Add 1 tablespoon herbmixture and 1 tablespoon oil to vegetables. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; toss to coat. Thread 1 mini pepper, 1 zucchini round, 1eggplant piece, 1 tomato, 1 onion piece, and 1 more mini pepper onto each of 8 skewers. DO AHEAD:  Herb mixture and vegetables can be made 4 hours ahead. Cover separately and refrigerate.'),
('3649', '4', 'Place fish in medium bowl; sprinkle 2 tablespoons herb mixture over.'),
('3649', '5', 'Add 3 tablespoons oil, 3 tablespoons lemon juice, and garlic; sprinkle with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Cover and chill at least 1 hour and up to 2 hours, tossing occasionally.'),
('3649', '6', 'Simmer wine, remaining 1 tablespoon oil, and remaining 2 tablespoons lemon juice in small saucepan until reduced to 1/3 cup, about 3 minutes. Stir in remaining herb mixture. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside.'),
('3649', '7', 'Spray grill rack with nonstick spray; prepare barbecue (medium-high heat). Divide fish cubes among remaining 4 skewers. Grill vegetable skewers until vegetables are slightly charred and tender, turning occasionally, 10 to 12 minutes. Grill fish skewers until fish is cooked through, turning occasionally, 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('3649', '8', 'Place 1 fish skewer and 2 vegetable skewers on each plate.'),
('3649', '9', 'Drizzle sauce over.'),
('3649', '10', '* Also called culinary lavender buds;available at some supermarkets andfarmers'' markets, at many natural foodsstores, and from deandeluca.com.'),
('3652', '1', 'Pulse fennel, onion, and garlic in a food processor until coarsely chopped.'),
('3652', '2', 'Heat oil in a 5- to 6-quart heavy pot over medium-high heat until it shimmers, then stir in chopped vegetables, bay leaves, thyme, red-pepper flakes, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper.'),
('3652', '3', 'Cook, covered, over medium heat, stirring once or twice, until vegetables begin to soften, about 4 minutes.'),
('3652', '4', 'Add tomatoes with their juice, water, wine, and clam juice and boil, covered,  20 minutes. Stir in seafood and cook, uncovered, until fish is just cooked through and mussels open wide, 4 to 6 minutes (discard any that remain unopened after 6 minutes). Discard bay leaves.'),
('3652', '5', 'Nutrition Data'),
('3652', '6', 'See Nutrition Data''s complete analysis of this recipe '),
('3656', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 400F. Bring a large pot of water to a boil and add salt.'),
('3656', '2', 'Cut the lemons in half and squeeze the juice into the salted water. Drop in the shells.'),
('3656', '3', 'Add the artichoke hearts, carrots, and fennel. Cook until all the vegetables are tender, about 12 minutes.'),
('3656', '4', 'Drain and spread on a baking sheet to cool.'),
('3656', '5', 'Season the fish steaks on both sides with salt and pepper and then season each steak with  teaspoon of the herbs.'),
('3656', '6', 'Heat the olive oil in a heavy, ovenproof saut pan over medium-high heat until hot.'),
('3656', '7', 'Add the fish and sear for about 2 minutes on each side.'),
('3656', '8', 'Remove the fish to a plate.'),
('3656', '9', 'Replace the pan over medium-high heat and add the artichokes, carrots, and fennel. Season with salt and pepper and the remaining  teaspoon herbes de Provence. Saut until brown, about 3 minutes.'),
('3656', '10', 'Arrange the fish on top of the vegetables and place the pan, uncovered, in the oven to finish cooking, about 10 minutes.'),
('3656', '11', 'When cooked, remove the fish and vegetables to a warm platter and keep warm while you make the sauce.'),
('3656', '12', 'Place the saut pan over medium-high heat and add the wine. Bring to a boil, stirring and scraping all the browned bits from the bottom and sides of the pan. Cook until reduced by about two-thirds (this is a brothy sauce).'),
('3656', '13', 'Stir in the fennel leaves and the butter, if using. Taste for seasoning and pour over the fish.'),
('3656', '14', 'Serve immediately.'),
('3657', '1', 'Place fish pieces in a bowl, add the minced garlic and lime juice so that the pieces are well coated. Sprinkle generously all over with salt and pepper.Keep chilled while preparing the rest of the soup.2 Make rice for serving with soup:If you are planning on serving the soup with rice, start on the rice.Bring a couple cups of water to a boil.'),
('3657', '2', 'Heat one Tbsp of olive oil in a medium saucepan on medium high heat.'),
('3657', '3', 'Add the chopped 1/2 onion and cook, stirring, until the onion is translucent.'),
('3657', '4', 'Add the garlic and cook for 30 seconds more, until the garlic is fragrant.'),
('3657', '5', 'Add the raw white rice and stir to coat completely with the oil, onions, and garlic.'),
('3657', '6', 'Add the boiling water. (The amount depends on your brand of rice, check the package. If no amounts are given, add 1 3/4 cup of water for every cup of rice.) Stir in 1 teaspoon of salt.Bring to a simmer, then lower the heat, cover, and let cook for 15 minutes, after which, remove from heat until ready to serve with the soup.3 Start cookingthe onion, bell pepper, tomatoes, onion greens:In a large covered pan (such as a Dutch oven), coat the bottom with about 2 Tbsp of olive oil and heat on medium heat.'),
('3657', '7', 'Add the chopped onion and cook a few minutes until softened.'),
('3657', '8', 'Add the bell pepper, paprika, and red pepper flakes. Sprinkle generously with salt and pepper. (At least a teaspoon of salt.) Cook for a few minutes longer, until the bell pepper begins to soften.Stir in the chopped tomatoes and onion greens. Bring to a simmer and cook for 5 minutes, uncovered. Stir in the chopped cilantro.3 Layer vegetables with fish, add coconut milk: Use a large spoon to remove about half of the vegetables (you''ll put them right back in).'),
('3657', '9', 'Spread the remaining vegetables over the bottom of the pan to create a bed for the fish. Arrange the fish pieces on the vegetables. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Then add back the previously removed vegetables, covering the fish.'),
('3657', '10', 'Pour coconut milk over the fish and vegetables.4 Simmer, cook, adjust seasonings:Bring soup to a simmer, reduce the heat, cover, and let simmer for 15 minutes. Taste and adjust seasonings.You may need to add more salt (likely), lime or lemon juice, paprika, pepper, or chili flakes to get the soup to the desired seasoning for your taste.'),
('3657', '11', 'Garnish with cilantro.'),
('3657', '12', 'Serve with rice or with crusty bread.'),
('3661', '1', 'Preheat oven to 300 degrees.'),
('3661', '2', 'Spread 2 tablespoons reserved charmoula over the bottom of a tagine; sprinkle with carrots and celery.'),
('3661', '3', 'Add half of the tomatoes and bell peppers; top with fish and drizzle with some of the charmoula.'),
('3661', '4', 'Add remaining tomatoes and bell peppers and spread remaining charmoula over top.'),
('3662', '1', 'Stir the saffron into the mayonnaise; season with salt and pepper. Toss the watercress, fennel, shallot and lemon juice; season.'),
('3662', '2', 'Melt the butter in the oil in a skillet. Season the fish with salt and pepper; cook over high heat for 3 minutes per side.'),
('3662', '3', 'Spread the bread with the saffron mayonnaise; sprinkle with paprika. Fill the sandwiches with the fish, peppers, tomato and watercress salad, and serve.'),
('3663', '1', 'Combine fish and 1/2 cup lime juice in a stainless steel or glass bowl. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes. (The fish will overcure and have a mushy texture if you exceed 30 minutes.)'),
